Job Description
Working at IRSC has its perks! In addition to helping drive change and having a positive impact by supporting our students, staff, and faculty, IRSC offers a comprehensive benefits package including:
Medical, Dental, Vision, Life Insurance, and Flexible Spending
Paid time off, including annual and sick leave and paid holidays
Florida Retirement System (FRS) participation
Voluntary participation in 403(b) and 457(b) deferred compensation plans
QUALIFICATIONS, KNOWLEDGE AND SKILL REQUIREMENTS:
The qualifications and skill requirements position include:
Associate’s degree from an accredited institution;
Minimum of three (3) years of proven work experience in an administrative assistant or secretarial position;
Excellent communication skills – both verbal and written;
Excellent computer skills including strong foundation in Microsoft Office applications, including Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint, and various office software;
Excellent organizational and interpersonal skills as well as the ability to multi-task;
Ability to work with people in pressure situations;
Ability to work independently as well as with student, faculty, staff and co-workers and be self-motivated;
Valid Florida Driver’s License;
As this position works directly with college administrators, faculty, staff, general public, and students on a regular basis via telephone, e-mail, and in-person, the ability to interact positively with others is essential;
Absolute discretion in the handling and management of faculty and student files and issues;
Understanding of FERPA, HIPPA, and other laws and college policies requiring confidentiality;
The following is preferred:
Master’s degree or higher from an accredited institution in an Industrial Arts, Career & Technical Education field, or Vocational Education field;
ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
The essential job functions and responsibilities for this position include, but are not limited to:
Functioning as office manager and receptionist for Workforce Education;
Processing Period Activity Pay for full-time faculty as well as adjuncts;
Organizing and arranging meetings both on-line and in-person;
Mentoring and overseeing the work of Work Study students and part-time employees on a daily basis;
Making reservations for rooms and labs;
Collecting, maintaining, and assisting with faculty course schedules;
Creating and cancelling courses;
Assisting in the resolution of student issues in Workforce Education & Advanced Technology programs;
Assisting with advisement and registration of Workforce Education & Advanced Technology programs.
SPECIFIC DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
The specific duties and responsibilities for this position include, but are not limited to:
Organizing and maintaining Dean’s schedule and appointments;
Handling incoming phone calls and e-mails;
Entering and processing electronic reports, requisitions, work orders, travel authorizations, petty cash, registrations, letters, memos, and processing Period Activity Pay for full-time faculty overload, adjunct teaching credit and clock hour courses, and substitution payments;
Responsible to his/her Dean for effective organization and professionalism within the Dean’s office;
Prepare e-mails, letters and other correspondence that reflect the professional nature of a state college;
Process and handle all types of mail and packages;
Operating and/or utilizing a variety of office machines and equipment;
Maintain a list of daily events and obligations;
Maintaining an accurate filing system of records, evaluations, syllabi, grade forms, instructor schedules, and other important documents;
Demonstrate MS Word, MS Excel, MS Outlook proficiency and professionalism;
Completing other duties as assigned by the Dean of Workforce Education.
PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:
The physical requirements for this position include:
Ability to regularly lift and or move up to 25 pounds, frequently lift and/or move up to 50 pounds, and occasionally lift and/or move up to 50 pounds; Ability to sit, stand, walk, bend, reach up, stoop; Manual dexterity and balance required to operate standard office machines such as copier, fax, calculator, telephone, and other equipment as necessary; IRSC expects its employees to follow proper safety standards while employed by the College.
